    "description": "Missing validation of delegation token expiry timestamp. When a delegation token is retrieved for authentication (line 121), the tokenExpiryTimestamp is stored but never validated against the current time. This allows an attacker to use an expired delegation token for authentication if the callback handler returns an expired token. The authentication should fail immediately if the token has expired.",
