    "file": "clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/security/authenticator/CredentialCache.java",
    "line": 25,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "Type confusion vulnerability in CredentialCache.createCache(). When createCache() is called with a mechanism that already has a cached instance, it returns the existing cache without validating that the credential class matches. This allows code to request a cache of type X for a mechanism, but receive a cache of type Y that was created earlier. This can lead to ClassCastException or authentication/authorization bypass if mismatched credential types are used.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/security/authenticator/CredentialCache.java
+++ b/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/security/authenticator/CredentialCache.java
@@ -26,7 +26,10 @@
     public <C> Cache<C> createCache(String mechanism, Class<C> credentialClass) {
         Cache<C> cache = new Cache<>(credentialClass);
         @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
         Cache<C> oldCache = (Cache<C>) cacheMap.putIfAbsent(mechanism, cache);
-        return oldCache == null ? cache : oldCache;
+        Cache<C> resultCache = oldCache == null ? cache : oldCache;
+        if (resultCache.credentialClass() != credentialClass)
+            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid credential class " + credentialClass + ", expected " + resultCache.credentialClass());
+        return resultCache;
     }

     @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
"
